subject_prompt_600:
Il sole nella pioggia is an Italian song from the opera, Il trattato del mondo (The Three Musketeers), written by Giuseppe Verdi.

This song was published in 1913 on the "L'Annee Opera" in Paris by Mascagni and played for the first time on March 26, 1912. It was included in the first edition of The Three Musketeers published in 1913 (the second edition had an additional scene at Venice). It later appeared in two radio broadcasts on May 18 and 19, 1914. A film version premiered on January 23, 1917.

This song is part of the series of songs known as the Pied Piper Series.
